===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|palais|lang=fro}}, which comes from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|palātium|lang=la}}, from {{term|Palātium|lang=la}}, in reference to the [[Palatine]] Hill, one of the seven hills of Rome, where the aristocracy of the Roman [[republic|Republic]]—and later, Roman emperors—built large, splendid residences. The name is ultimately either from {{etyl|ett|en}}, the same source as {{term|Pales||{{w|Pales}}, the Italic goddess of shepherds, flocks and livestock|lang=la}}, or Latin {{term|palus||stake; enclosure|lang=la}}.

